programme.desc:
On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we head to Kansas with the father-son duo in Justin and Nolan Redeker for the epic story of the "Lost Tine Buck". Before that, however, we catch up with Owen Reigler in Iowa to see one of the craziest buck encounters we have ever seen here at Midwest Whitetail. Be sure to drop your best nickname suggestion in the comments below for the chance to win an awesome Chasing November apparel package!
For Justin and Nolan Redeker, the hunting lifestyle is one that began many years ago. A fire that was lit by his dad at a young age, the passion for deer hunting burned hot for Justin, eventually becoming something he passed down to son Nolan down the road. Since then, the duo have shared many great experiences in the outdoors, all leading up to a windy October 12th that saw Justin tag a true Kansas monster with Nolan behind the lens. A story that will go down as one of our favorites, the footage speaks for itself when we say this is one you don't want to miss! Thank you as always for taking the time to watch and good luck out there.

programme.title: 181" MONARCH FALLS - The Story of "Genesis"
programme.desc: On this episode of Midwest Whitetail, Owen Reigler takes us along on the four year quest for an Iowa monarch he calls "Genesis." Before jumping into the story, however, Josh Sparks gives a quick update on a monster Kansas buck that Justin Redeker was able to tag with son Nolan Redeker behind the camera. Season after season, no matter the bucks around to hunt, Owen Reigler prides himself on year-round preparation of his farm, honing his archery skills and attention to all the details to create hunting opportunities for mature bucks. A shining example of this, the four year saga that saw the "Genesis" buck slowly call Owen's farm home represents a story of hard work, gratitude and enjoyment of the outdoors unlike anyone else. With an ending only the footage itself can tell, this is one you don't want to miss! Congratulations to Owen once again, and we are excited to continue bringing you more big buck action as we continue into the month of October. Good luck and happy hunting!

programme.title: The Ultimate Bully Buck
programme.desc: Back with another mid-week show, today's episode of Midwest Whitetail finds the Reed family back in the woods on a successful early October hunt. Before diving into the hunt for "Tony," Mike Reed discusses tips on how to identify bully bucks, and how continuing to focus on harvesting mature bucks year after year keeps the herd hierarchy in balance and optimizes herd structure. Then, battling the early October heatwave, Mike and his two sons Tate and Xander hit the River Farm with the legendary buck "Tony" at the top of the target list. Coming down to the wire, Tate makes a perfect shot leading to another great memory made in the deer woods. We thank you as always for your support and hope you enjoy the show!
